1. *Priznaj* mi istinu. (Adressed directly to someone, meaning "Admit the truth to me.")
2. On *priznaje* svoju ljubav prema njoj. (Subject of the sentence, meaning "He admits his love for her.")
3. Ja sam *priznao* svoju grešku. (Subject of the sentence, past tense, meaning "I admitted my mistake.")
4. Ti si *priznala* da si pogrešila. (Subject of the sentence, past tense, feminine gender, meaning "You admitted that you were wrong.")
5. Oni će *priznavati* svoju krivicu. (Future tense, meaning "They will admit their guilt.")
6. Da li ćeš *priznati* istinu? (Infinitive, asking a question, meaning "Will you admit the truth?")
7. Sada kada *priznaš* istinu, sve će biti bolje. (Second person singular, future tense, meaning "Now that you admit the truth, everything will be better.")
8. *Priznavši* svoju grešku, dobio je drugu šansu. (Past tense, participle, meaning "By admitting his mistake, he got a second chance.")
9. *Priznaj* da si pogrešio i nećeš biti kažnjen. (Imperative, addressing someone, meaning "Admit that you were wrong and you won't be punished.")
10. Nakon što je *priznao* svoje greške, krenuo je dalje. (Past tense, meaning "After admitting his mistakes, he moved on.")